=> CDI
  contexts and dependency injection
=> Java bean
  class that encapsulates one or more objects into a single standardized object. It enables reuse of
  the class without needing to know its implementation details.(serializable,have zero argument constructor, allow 
  access to properties via getters and setters.
=> Serialization
  conversion of an object into a byte stream that can be stored or transported and later on be 
  restored to the initial object.
=> url safe
  a token / string can be used in a url because it carries no meaningful face value


